The paper deals with fundamental problems in graph theory, specifically minimum cuts and shortest cycles in directed planar graphs. The algorithmic techniques used involve divide-and-conquer and noncrossing shortest paths, which are common in computational geometry and discrete mathematics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves optimization and graph theory, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
